<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
  
@!component('components.head', title="Teacher Allocation System")
@!component('components.header')
<body>  
  <section class="section">
    <div class="container">
      <h1 class="title">
        Help
      </h1>
      <p class="subtitles">
        <b>Here is the guide to Teacher Allocation System.</b>
      </p>
      <p class="subheading">
        You can start with allocating academics with the <b>Start Importing Button</b>.</p>      </p>

      <div class="tab">
        <button class="tablinks" onclick="openfunc(event, 'Import')" id="defaultOpen">Import</button>
        <button class="tablinks" onclick="openfunc(event, 'Export')">Export</button>
        <button class="tablinks" onclick="openfunc(event, 'Colour Tags')">Colour Tags</button>
        <button class="tablinks" onclick="openfunc(event, 'Allocations')">Allocations</button>
        <button class="tablinks" onclick="openfunc(event, 'Academics')">Academics</button>
        <button class="tablinks" onclick="openfunc(event, 'Units')">Units</button>
      </div>
    </div>
    
    
    <!-- Tab content -->
<div id="Import" class="tabcontent">
  <h3><b> Import: </b></h3>
  <p>You can import your spreadsheet filled with the details of the academics and Units by:</p>
  <ol>
    <li> Click on the <b>Choose file</b> button.</li>
    <li> Select an excel file from your local computer(make sure its an xml file).</li>
    <li> Submit the excel file by clicking on the <b>Submit</b> button.</li>
  </ol>
</div>


<div id="Export" class="tabcontent">

  <h3><b> Export: </b></h3>
  <p>You can export a year's spreadsheet to an excel spreadsheet by:</p>
  <ol>
    <li> Choose a year you want to export the spreadsheet from the drop down option.</li>
    <li> Then click on the <b>Submit</b> button.</li>
    <li> Click in the download. Your spreadsheet will be download in an excel file.</li>
  </ol>
</div>

<div id="Colour Tags" class="tabcontent">

  <h3><b> Colour Tags: </b></h3>
  <p>Coloured Tags corresponds to the relation between the request load and the actual load.</p>
  <dl>
    <dt style ="color: red"> <b>Red Tag:</b></dt>
    <li> The actual load is more than the requested load.</li>
    
    <dt style ="color: orange"><b>Orange Tag:</b></dt>
    <li> The actual load is less than the requested load.</li>

    <dt style="color:green"><b>Green Tag:</b></dt>
    <li> The actual load matches the requested load.</li>

  </dl>
</div>

  <div id="Allocations" class="tabcontent">

    <h3><b> Allocations: </b></h3>
    <p>You can either search or add for Allocations:</p>
    <ol>
      <dt> <b><u>Search Allocation:</u></b></dt>
      <li> Choose a year you want to search for allocation from the drop down option.</li>
      <li> Then click on the <b>Search</b> button.</li>
      <li> You can also search for a particular allocation from the search bar. Then click on the <b>Search</b> button.</li>
    </ol>
    <dt> <b><u>Add Allocation:</u></b></dt>

  </div>

  <div id="Academics" class="tabcontent">

    <h3><b> Academics: </b></h3>
    <p>You can either search or add academics:</p>
    <dt> <b><u>Search Academics:</u></b></dt>
    <ol>
      <li> Choose a year you want to view the academic data from the drop down option.</li>
      <li> Then click on the <b>Search</b> button.</li>
      <li> You can even view less or more data by removing or entering tags from the <b>Find academic</b> search bar.</li>
    </ol>
    <dt> <b><u>Add Academics:</u></b></dt>
    <p> You can add academics by selecting the <b> Add Academic +</b> button.</p>
    <ol>
      <li> Fill out the following details to add an academic.</li>      
      
      <li> After filling out the details click on the Add academic button.</li>
      <li> Your academic is successfully added.</li>
    </ol>
  </div>

  <div id="Units" class="tabcontent">

    <h3><b> Units: </b></h3>
    <p>You can either search or add Units:</p>
    <dt> <b><u>Search Units:</u></b></dt>
    <ol>
      <li> Choose a year you want to view the units data from the drop down option.</li>
      <li> Then click in the <b>Search</b> button.</li>
      <li> You can even view less or more data by removing or entering tags from the <b>Find Unit</b> search bar .</li>
    </ol>
    <dt> <b><u>Add Units:</u></b></dt>
    <p> You can add units by selecting the <b> Add Units +</b> button.</p>
    <ol>
      <li> Fill out the following details to add a unit.</li>      
      
      <li> After filling out the details click on the Add unit button.</li>
      <li> Your unit is successfully added.</li>
    </ol>
  </div>



<script>
  function openfunc(evt, functionality) {
    var i, tabcontent, tablinks;
    tabcontent = document.getElementsByClassName("tabcontent");
    for (i = 0; i < tabcontent.length; i++) {
      tabcontent[i].style.display = " none ";
    }
    tablinks = document.getElementsByClassName("tablinks");
    for (i = 0; i < tablinks.length; i++) {
      tablinks[i].className = tablinks[i].className.replace("active", "");
    }
    document.getElementById(functionality).style.display = "block";
    evt.currentTarget.className += "active";
  }
  document.getElementById("defaultOpen").click();
  </script>


  </section>

  






  </body>
  
  
  



  @include('partials.footer')

</html>
